title: Meet Kylie Jenner’s $69K dog
text:
Email a friend 
Kylie Jenner and Tyga may not have kids yet, but they’re parents to a new puppy. 
According to TMZ, the couple was gifted a $US50,000 ($AUD 69,000) merle tri English Bulldog, named Rolly, on Thursday. Rolly 
PingTank CEO Jeremy Greene sent over the pup, which came from Shrinkabulls.com, an English and French Bulldogs breeding company. 
Pooches from the site range from $3,000 to $30,000 each. Rolly 
Kylie and Tyga join a list of celebrities who’ve gotten puppies from the company including Iggy Azalea and fiance Nick Young, NFL star Troy Polamalu, Randy Jackson and Chris Brown. 
But of course Rolly won’t be lonely — he joins Kylie’s Italian Greyhounds Norman and Bambie.
